1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 dxc4 {starting position for Vienna -
variation of Queen Gambit Declined. Fabolous line , used by famous players
amongst them Kasparov, Anand , Karpov, Tal and Ribli. The most powerful score
is of Armenian GM Levon Aronian , + 7 = 12, Well known names are Arkadij
Najditch, Loek Van Wely , Y.Yakovich, A.Kharlov, and Hungarian GM Z.Gyimesi.
The line is known by its forced character ,black takes the pawn on c4 with the
idea to counterattack white central pawns with Bb4 and c5} 5. Bg5 (5. Qa4+ {
White is trying to avoid the forced variations and to stay on positional
grounds . But after} Nbd7 6. e4 a6 7. Bxc4 Rb8 $1 {play soon takes the typical
for Meran dynamic stream Chapter- 1 -}) (5. e3 {Positional line - Chapter-2
White shows his peaceful intentions I recommend here for black} a6 $1 6. a4 b6
7. Bxc4 Bb7 {as our best try to keep a playable position in the same time
avoiding drawish tendencies of queen gambit accepted}) (5. e4 Bb4 6. Bxc4 {
extremely dangerous sacrificial line} Nxe4 {we take the pawn and I believe
that black defense is not that difficult} 7. O-O Nxc3 8. bxc3 Be7 {Chapter - 3
- White has 4 main plans - I consider the most dangerous to be Qe2 followed by
Rd1 -Aronian -Wang Hao 2014 planning the rook lift Rd1-d3-h3} 9. Qe2) 5... Bb4
6. e4 (6. Qa4+ {-Is sharp options to avoid the main line and still pressure
black at an early stage Chapter-4} Nc6 7. e4 Bd7 8. Qc2 h6 $1 {and black is
fine} (8... b5 $2 {pay attention to this subtle moment - this obvious move is
losing in a straightforward way} 9. e5 h6 10. exf6 hxg5 11. fxg7 Rg8 12. Qh7
Ne7 (12... Ke7 13. O-O-O) 13. Ne5 c5 14. Be2 $1)) 6... c5 7. Bxc4 (7. e5 {
leads either to a super sharp and crazy position after} cxd4 8. Qa4+ ({either
easy equality after} 8. Nxd4 Qa5 9. exf6 Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 Qxg5 11. fxg7 Qxg7 12.
Qd2 O-O) 8... Nc6 9. O-O-O Bd7 10. Ne4 Be7 11. exf6 gxf6 12. Bh4 a6 13. Qxc4 e5
{Chapter-5}) 7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bxc3+ $1 {black has other options as well but I
like very much this concrete approach.} (8... Qa5 $5 {is what I played in 5
games with an overall score of + 2 -1 =4. One of my best achievements is my
victory over French GM Bacrot in 29 Moves}) 9. bxc3 Qa5 10. Bb5+ (10. Nb5 {Was
white main weapon some 30 years ago .Nowadays is considered harmless -Chapter-6
}) (10. Bxf6 {Is not at all disturbing if we avoid the tricks after} Qxc3+ 11.
Kf1 gxf6 $1 {Chapter-7} (11... Qxc4+ $6 12. Kg1) 12. Rc1 Qa5 $1 {keeps the
game in aproximately equal chances} (12... Qb4 {is typical mistake because of}
13. Bxe6 ({or even} 13. Nb5 {seems rather unpleasant}))) 10... Nbd7 11. Bxf6 {
white only move} (11. O-O Nxe4) (11. Qd3 O-O) 11... Qxc3+ 12. Kf1 (12. Ke2 {
pay attention to this moment we should play} Qb2+ $1 (12... gxf6 $6 13. Rc1)
13. Kf1 gxf6) 12... gxf6 13. h4 $1 ({or} 13. Rc1 Qb4 14. h4) 13... a6 14. Rh3
Qb4 15. Be2 Ne5 $1 {and according to my analisis black is doing fine Main Line
-chapter -8} *

