1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 dxc4 5. e4 Bb4 6. Bxc4 $5 {Very important
line. Here White sacrifices a pawn for a long-term compensation based on piece
activity and space advantage} (6. Bg5 {This is the main line which will be
covered in the following chapters}) 6... Nxe4 {There is no better move than
taking the pawn here.} 7. O-O Nxc3 8. bxc3 Be7 {White has four different
options to organize the attack. We will cover all of them in the following
games.} 9. Re1 {This move was Veselin Topalov's idea.} (9. Qc2) (9. Qe2 {
Aronian's line}) (9. Ne5 O-O 10. Qg4 {Main line}) *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
